            <h2>FAQ</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="full-width-content">
            <Accordion variant='splitted' title="Bosch Washer Repair FAQ">
              <AccordionItem title="How long do Bosch washers typically last?">
                <p>With proper care, Bosch washers can last 12–15 years or more.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Why is my Bosch washer showing an E17 error code?">
                <p>This usually indicates a water inlet problem — often caused by a clogged filter or faulty inlet valve.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Can I clean a Bosch washer's drain pump myself?">
                <p>Yes, Bosch provides access to the filter for basic cleaning, but if the pump itself is faulty, it's best to have a technician replace it.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Is Bosch washer repair more expensive than other brands?">
                <p>Bosch parts can be slightly more costly due to their precision engineering, but repairs are often worth it given the brand's quality.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
            </Accordion>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-9">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
